          Hey people, Joe here.<br /><br />E3R is sorta in limbo at the moment because our domain, dform.org, expires today. Right now Comcast is being retarded and I won't have internet access until Wednesday. "Well you could go use the library's internet access" is what I'm sure a lot of you are saying. However, my roof fell on my 600$ couch and the whole living room was infested with black and green mold. My idiotic landlord is taking 3 weeks until he can get a roofer out to begin working on our place *no doubt* because he doesn't want to spend more money on a professional. I can't wait till I'm away from this guy. Nice guy to speak to but he's just an ass. There is also leaks in the master bedroom, with steams imprinted on the bricks of the wall. We first noticed them when we noticed piece of brick, in a fine dust form, on my dresser. I took my thumb to investigate the walls further and my thumb took off a huge flake of brick with little force. <br /><br />More or less, my apartment is in ruins.<span style="font-weight:bold;"> Anyway, pay attention.</span> I can either renew dform.org or get another domain instead that makes more sense. How about e3rd.com? ya know...e as in electronic and 3rd as in "third"? no? How about e-3rd.com? Better? Eh, I need some help here people. Comment on this post and tell me which you like better.<br /><br />Furthermore, I just found out that my bill for school is due on Thursday, the first day of classes and I won't find out my estimated loan total until Wednesday. Mind you, I still have to change one of my classes to German 101. I'd really like that. Anyhoo, I gotta head back to the lab. <br /><br />How much would you all be pissed if I changed this layout a bit? It's very heavy...taking a whopping 5 seconds to load on the library's T1-powered LAN. Send your comments on that too while you're at it, skags.<br /><br />That's right...I called you all 'skags'. <span style="font-style:italic;">Oldschool</span>.<br />
