     <font class="TallRed">Mirror Metaphysics<a name="109315472575239199">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          I know what you mean Venus.  Lately, when I look in the mirror it's like I'm looking at someone else.  I don't mean to say that I don't recognize myself, I'm talking more about the act of looking.  I've always had this weird ability to see what someone's going to look like when they're older.  At least I assume it still works, I guessed right for my friends' transitions into teenagerdom.  I don't notice anything physical in particular, I read into what I see.  I imagine kind of an overlay, like adding an alpha channel to an image.  It's because of that dynamic that things seem wrong when it comes to myself.<br /><br />When I look at a mirror I read into the image and become lost in thought.  Then I snap out of it and take myself at face value, and realize that I'm 20 years old.  Young, yes, but beyond the age of excuses.  That person can't be me, can't be as I have been.  That person has to grow up and live.  He doesn't have the luxury to, say, write something like this.  That's what really bothers me, way more than the fact that I'm standing around looking in a mirror.  I have to change and I don't want to.  I don't fear change, and I'm not really hesitant or scared.  I like planning, I like thinking, I HATE doing.  I'm bound to fuck something up if I do it, I'm destined to at least be injured.  Not being to stand, walk, or do pretty much anything else stably will do that to you.  It makes you manipulate your own thinking, even though you know you're full of shit.  And that's what it comes down to when I look in the mirror, I see myself facing these things.  I see me looking back at me, and I don't see the truth.  Come to think of it, maybe I don't know how you feel Venus.<br /><br />Disclaimer:  Now that I've written all this it feels like complete bullshit, but I'm posting it anyway since I must have written it for a reason.<br />
          <div class="byline">
